&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are heycar&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Since August 2019, we’ve been making it easier for customers to find the right vehicle, and for automotive retailers to sell them.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;More recently, we’ve been on a journey…&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In June 2025 we were acquired by Volkswagen Financial Services UK (VWFS UK) and our mission is simple: build the right tech solutions for Volkswagen Group UK and its retailers, so they can deliver the best possible experiences to their customers.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re a mix of problem-solvers, innovators, and team players who care about doing great work and making a difference. We thrive on collaboration, innovation, and a shared commitment to excellence. We deliver impactful solutions at pace that put the customer at the centre.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you&#39;re looking for a meaningful challenge, and want to help shape the future of automotive experiences, then read on…&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the role:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for a Product Manager to help us redefine our core platform capabilities. In this role, you’ll sit in the engine room of our technical ecosystem, ensuring our platform seamlessly integrates with critical upstream and downstream systems to drive deep operational and business value.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working on the core backend architecture, you’ll tackle technical and data-heavy challenges. Instead of tweaking frontend flows or optimising user interfaces, you will focus on building robust infrastructure, data pipelines, and system integrations. You’ll own the entire product lifecycle: from planning and technical requirements definition to managing complex backend backlogs and delivering platform features that move the needle.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you’re a problem-solver who thrives on technical complexity, loves mapping out elegant data transformation solutions, and wants to leave a tangible mark on a fast-evolving platform, we’d love to talk.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the Integration Roadmap: Take ownership of specific backend and integration domains within cross-functional squads, acting as the subject matter expert for our platform&#39;s core connectivity and system dependencies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Map &amp;amp; Transform Data: Define and document technical requirements for mapping APIs, transforming data seamlessly from one format to another to ensure reliable, scalable, and performant system communication.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate Technical Vision: Convert data architecture and integration needs into actionable backend user stories, keeping data integrity and platform health at the heart of every decision.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive Reporting &amp;amp; Data Requirements: Define, implement, and track robust reporting metrics to ensure system health, data quality, and business performance are fully visible across the organization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage Vendor &amp;amp; System Stakeholders: Act as the primary product contact for third-party stakeholders and internal system owners, aligning integration requirements and managing delivery dependencies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Core Engineering: Collaborate closely with Backend Engineering, Architecture, and Data squads to design scalable, future-proof integration patterns and robust data contracts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll need:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Product Expertise: Proven track record as a Product Manager within Agile squads, with a knack for translating high-level platform goals into highly structured backend user stories.&l

